The following code doesn't seem to do the trick.

    private boolean isOutlookQuotedLine(String line) {
        InputStream outlookMessageProperties =  ClassLoaderUtils.getResourceAsStream("outlook-email.translations", this.getClass());
        if (line != null) {
            String message;
            try {
                BufferedReader messages = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(outlookMessageProperties));
                message = messages.readLine();
            } catch (Throwable t) {// no more properties
                return false;
            }
            if (line.indexOf(message) != -1)
                return true;
        }

        return false;
    }

Unless I am totally missing something here, won't this read only the first line of outlook-email.translations file?

This method is called to check against the message separators (in a reply email), so adding all the lines you can to that file is all you need to do (theoretically) to update for new email message separators.

I simply used a while loop to loop over the entire file, reading one line in at a time.

- Shawn Windler

